The paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning algorithms for autonomous driving, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of deep learning techniques such as deep deterministic policy gradient (DDPG) and the evaluation of performance in simulation-based scenarios suggest that the paper may also fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The focus on driving and stopping behaviors suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the use of reinforcement learning for control suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
